author: Suhas Nayse
title: Twin titles for Samarth Vyayam Shala spikers
text:
NAGPUR: Both the men's and women's teams of Samarth Vyayam Shala emerged champions in the 46th Nagpur District Volleyball Championship at the Anand Nagar Sports Association ground, Sakkardara, here on Thursday.
In the women's final, Samarth trounced Kolbaswami Dhapewada 25-18, 25-23, 25-19. Bhagyashri Dharmik, Sapna Meshram, Bhagyashree Rokde, Vaibhavi Jabalpure and Sweeti Nikose excelled.
In the men's title clash, Samarth outclassed Youth Sports Club, Katol 25-17, 25-23, 25-22, thanks to brilliant display by Yogesh Rao, Kunal Singh, Vedant Thavre, Rohit Sherje, Parth Tiwari, Hemant Nistane and Shivam Kale.
MLA Sudhakar Kohale, vice-president of Volleyball Federation of India Vijay Dangre and NDVA secretary Sunil Hande distributed the prizes. Stay updated on the go with Times of India News App. Click here to download it for your device.
